HEADWORD: Echidnine
<hw>E*chid"nine</hw> <pr>(?; 104)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Echidna</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The clear, viscid fluid
secreted by the poison glands of certain serpents; also, a nitrogenous
base contained in this, and supposed to be the active poisonous
principle of the virus.</def> <rj><au>Brande & C.</au></rj></p>

<p><ent>Echidnophaga</ent>⟦br⟧
